            <aside role="complementary" class=" content-aside newsfeed">
<h2>Latest News</h2>

            
<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194654-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/marketplace.aspx">Marketplace</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-16" itemprop="datePublished">7 Hours Ago</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194654/movie-industry-image-matches-year-high.aspx?g_source=Marketplace&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles"><strong>Movie Industry&rsquo;s</strong> Image in U.S. Matches 16-Year High</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">The movie industry's image in the U.S. ties for the most positive in Gallup's 16-year trend. Democrats' and younger adults' views of the industry have improved steadily since 2001.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194627-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/economy.aspx">Economy</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-16" itemprop="datePublished">13 Hours Ago</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194627/economic-confidence-index-largely-stable.aspx?g_source=Economy&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles"><strong>Economic Confidence</strong> Index Largely Stable at -12&nbsp;</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">The Gallup U.S. Economic Confidence Index averaged -12 last week, similar to the improved levels in the prior two weeks.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="cmstile tile-news type-speedbump" data-tileid="170987-PRODUCTS" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
<div class="tile-inner">
<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic">Analytics and Advice About Everything That Matters</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194624-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/politics.aspx">Politics</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-15" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 15, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194624/americans-approval-obama-foreign-affairs-rises.aspx?g_source=Politics&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles">Americans&rsquo; Approval of Obama on <strong>Foreign Affairs </strong>Rises</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">Nearly half of Americans (48%) approve of President Barack Obama's handling of foreign affairs in August -- up markedly from 39% in February. This rating is Obama's highest since November 2012, just days before he was re-elected.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194570-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/economy.aspx">Economy</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-15" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 15, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194570/restaurants-again-voted-popular-industry.aspx?g_source=Economy&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles">Restaurants Again Voted Most Popular <strong>U.S. Industry</strong></a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">Of 25 business and industry sectors, the restaurant industry has the top image score this year, with 66% of Americans rating it positively and only 7% negatively. Computers are a close second, while the federal government is dead last.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194567-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/election_2016.aspx">Election 2016</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-12" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 12, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194567/michelle-obama-popular-bill-clinton-melania-trump.aspx?g_source=Election 2016&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles"><strong>Michelle Obama</strong> More Popular Than Bill Clinton, Melania Trump</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">First lady Michelle Obama remains popular after the Democratic convention, while her potential successors as first spouse have image problems. Bill Clinton and Melania Trump are about as likely to be viewed positively as negatively.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194549-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/politics.aspx">Politics</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-12" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 12, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194549/americans-satisfaction-recovers-august-though-low.aspx?g_source=Politics&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles"><strong>Americans&rsquo; Satisfaction</strong> Recovers in August, Though Still Low</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">Americans' satisfaction with the way things are going in the U.S. is nearly back to where it was in June after a sharp drop in July. The rebound is chiefly attributable to declining concern about race relations and racism.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194552-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/election_2016.aspx">Election 2016</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-11" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 11, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194552/trump-clinton-favorability-back-pre-convention-levels.aspx?g_source=Election 2016&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles">Trump, Clinton <strong>Favorability</strong> Back to Pre-Convention Levels</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">Donald Trump's and Hillary Clinton's favorable ratings are almost exactly the same now as they were before their party's convention, despite some temporary movement as each convention unfolded.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194495-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/category_social_issues.aspx">Social Issues</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-11" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 11, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194495/obama-effect-racial-matters-falls-short-hopes.aspx?g_source=Social Issues&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles">In U.S., <strong>Obama Effect</strong> on Racial Matters Falls Short of Hopes</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">Americans' views of what President Barack Obama's election means for black progress and race relations are much less positive today, near the end of his presidency, than they were right after he was elected and early in his presidency.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194498-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/election_2016.aspx">Election 2016</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-10" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 10, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194498/views-political-parties-unchanged-conventions.aspx?g_source=Election 2016&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles">Views of U.S. <strong>Political Parties </strong>Unchanged After Conventions</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">Americans' opinions of the political parties are unchanged following both parties' conventions, with the Democratic Party maintaining a more positive image than the Republican Party.</p></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="cmstile tile-newslead type-release" data-tileid="194492-POLL" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle"><div class="tile-inner">

<div class="meta clearfix">
<div class="topic"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/topic/economy.aspx">Economy</a></div>
<time datetime="2016-08-10" itemprop="datePublished">Aug 10, 2016</time></div><div class="copy">

<div class="tile-linktext"><h3 itemprop="headline" data-overflow="ellipsis"><a href="/web/20160817021522/http://www.gallup.com/poll/194492/americans-assessment-job-market-slightly-worse.aspx?g_source=Economy&amp;g_medium=newsfeed&amp;g_campaign=tiles">Americans&rsquo; Assessment of <strong>U.S. Job Market </strong>Slightly Worse</a></h3></div>

<p class="item-synopsis" data-overflow="ellipsis">About four in 10 Americans (39%) in August say it is a good time to find a quality job, down slightly from 43% in July.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
